									<tr>
										<td colspan=2 valign="top">
										<div align=left><br><font class='header2'>Gordon Q & A</font><font class='small'>&nbsp;by randerson at 7/20/2000 4:20:00 PM PST</font><blockquote class='normal'><P class=normal>Gordon 'Abashi' Wrinn visited an EverQuest fan chat room this afternoon holding a long Q &amp; A session directly with the players. He went on to announce certain new upcoming changes with EverQuest including a much warranted change for a confirmation box when dropping items, making the majority of bards very happy. Below is a small portion of the session--click continue to view the full thing! EQanswers yet again brings this to you first!</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Baelish&gt; Abashi: was the cap for hannelling for casters increased in the latest patch, if so do you know the new cap?</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Bae: No, it wasn't.&nbsp; Who indicated that the channeling cap was being increased?</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Baelish&gt; weird</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Bae: Grrr.&nbsp; That wasn't on my list.&nbsp; I have to go give some programmers a hard time methinks.<BR><BR><EM>&lt;Strauss&gt; &lt;Enigmah&gt; Abashi: Any plans on fixing bugs that have been around since release such as the Gnome chain helms and various places where pathing is messed up <BR></EM><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>~&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Enigmah: Take a look at the last few patches, we've been fixing a number of very old bugs.&nbsp; I assume that you are speaking of the wholes in the gnomes head when he wears the helm, it's not a bug, just a graphics issue.&nbsp; Maybe we'll reload those textures at some point, but what we can do is limited by download size, and manpower that isn't better allocated elsewhere.</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Strauss&gt; &lt;DeaDlySin&gt; maybe this isnt a lame question, could u ask him if its posible to get a exp res once servers are down and brought back up?</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Deadlysin: The experience attached to a corpse is supposed to survive a server outage.&nbsp; The only problem I think was outstanding with experinece on corpses was death while linkdead.&nbsp; That should be solved now.</P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Oh, one new thing we havent' mentioned</P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> We're going to put in a item-drop confirmation with the next client.&nbsp; The original version won't have a way to turn it off, but perhaps a future one might.</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;frash&gt; BARDS EVERYWHERE WORSHIP YOU!</EM></P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Elderich&gt; Abashi: when you buy things and your inv is filled up, it will default to go into combine containers</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Elderich: Bah! If peopel are using combinable containers to store stuff that they don't want to combine, like using large sewing kits to carry halberds, they need that risk, or we have to nerf the containers</P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> I have to go chat with one of the programmers really quick, hang tight, be back in about a minute.</P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Ok, I'm back... I just went to get more information on the item-drop requester.&nbsp; Most bards know the problem of accidently dropping items between inventory slots.&nbsp; That problem will still occur, but instead of dropping the box will come up, just like when you hit destroy. If you are incombat at the time, or busy, you could certainly ignore the box until you get a free moment.&nbsp; The only time that an item iwll be dropped is if you have something on your cursor</P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> and hit yes.&nbsp; Money, however, will not bring up the confirmation since so many peopel like to drop copper and silver :)</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Quala&gt; will the confirmation box have a quick default like enter for yes?</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Quala: Does item destroy hav ea quick default for yes?&nbsp; If not, then no.</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Elderich&gt; Abashi: this should also solve exploits with trades right?</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Elderich: That too</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Elderich&gt; Abashi: wonderful</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Elder: YOu are talking about the one where the guy is dodging while you are trying to 'show' him an item, right?</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Elderich&gt; Abashi: that and the firepit</EM></P>
<P class=normal><FONT color=gold><STRONG>&lt;Abashi&gt;</STRONG></FONT> Well you'll definitely know if you've accidently clicked on the ground rather than another person.</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;JeffD&gt; abashi, any chance you guys will revamp vendor sold weapons and armor? its kinda nice many peoples weapons and armor in diablo2 are actually all vendor sold.. and the vendors change inv frequently so you may find a real good item or a oh hum item from time to time</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> JeffD: Probably not.&nbsp; We want to have people interacting with each other to get good stuff, not by interacting with a vendor.</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Baelish&gt; Abashi: Can you outline whats being done regarding the vox/nagafen changes and</EM> paladins. Will Snowdrift grow wings and fly off test?</P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Bae: Can't comment on any of those additional dragons that were spotted on Test.&nbsp; However, should we decide to leave Vox and Naggy as is (in regards to 53+) then it makes sense that we'd change the firey avenger quest.</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;melusina&gt; What you need to do is make Vox and Naggy fall in love and have little baby purple dragons =)</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Melusina: Naggy is a lava dragon, whereas Vox is an Ice dragon.&nbsp; That might not mix too well.</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Baelish&gt; Abashi: Do you know if EQLive are revising pathing/ai for Sebilis - theres serious problems with ilis/shroom trains and even aggro on entering on occasion.</EM></P>
<P class=normal><FONT color=gold><STRONG>&lt;Abashi&gt;</STRONG></FONT> Baelish: We've heard of the problems. Ester is working ot catalogue all of the problems at which time they can be looked at.&nbsp; Same with Karnor's, though Sebilis does have some worse problems.&nbsp; Some of them might not be solveable, and just become one of the risks of using the zone.</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;DeaDlySin&gt; Abashi: Do you know if the non melee dmg hit to a mob in text will be changed back to white from the awful blue that it is now?</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> DeadlySin: Being chagned to Yellow right now.</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Strauss&gt; &lt;Sanitize&gt; Hrm, I wanna know bout AC on monk plane/kunark armor. Will they be increased cause right now it seems pretty weak, and while other</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Sanitize: I've looked at them, and a few people have sent me notes about them, I think that they should be looked at since they don't seem to make much sense.&nbsp; However, not making much sense doesn't necessarily mean that there is a problem to be solved. Monks rock as is. That said, EQLive still needs to check them out.</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;JeffD&gt; abashi, why dont you guys use a patcher that instead of totaly replaces files.. alters files.? your file format are all packages of raw files (hence we can extract them).. so why not create a patcher that downloads only the changed and new data in the compressed package format.. and merge it with the fileso n your hard drive, or hard code it in the everchanging exe file and simply point to the new package files</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> JeffD: The format of most of the data doesn't lend itself very well to a realtime patch.&nbsp; The additional problem with RTPs is that if the file ever gets corrupted, you have to download the original version and every patch over again.&nbsp; Might as well keep it to the most recent files when possible.</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Strauss_&gt; &lt;Greldon&gt; Abashi, Yaulp 4 cancels death pact. Any clue if this is a bug or intentional, and if you're aware of it will it be fixed?</EM></P>
<P class=normal><FONT color=gold><STRONG>&lt;Abashi&gt;</STRONG></FONT> Greldon: I wasn't personally aware of the problem.&nbsp; Stop by the QA board and mention it.&nbsp; THe spells weren't purposely designed in that fashion, however the overwrite might be unavoidable given how spell-stacking works.&nbsp; We'd probably have to nerf one or the other to stop it.</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Baelish&gt; Abashi: Since you are editing thorns, can you changeit so that only the person with thorns on them receives the message about damage being inflicted? The current setup only serves to spam people nearby, and in large fights causes serious bandwidth issues for modem players.</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Baelish: Well the former (editing text messages) is quick, the latter takes coding. In any case, it's on my list for monday's meeting.&nbsp; Someone was nice enough to explain to me the spam created by having a bunch of warriors and rangers with twigs beat on a o'kieled NPC</P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Just as you suggested as well, ot only report it to the person taking the damage, rather than as a /emote</P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Kire&gt;</FONT></STRONG> &lt;Evilspoon&gt; Abashi&nbsp; With the patch yesterday, the icon for lava shield is now the same color as the icon for my fire based DDs.&nbsp; Will you be changing this back to yellow, instead of keeping it red, like my color of my fire DD icon, or should a buff look like a DD?</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Baelish&gt; Abashi: Can you confrim whether any players have been receiving item wipe/restores and if so how long ago the backup was done exp/item wise?</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Baelish: Niether is occuring.&nbsp; Weighing all of the options, we decided not to rollback character data.&nbsp; I posted about it on Flameplay today more in depth.</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;DaScott&gt; Abashi: the boards are crammed with people asking where the sky item upgrade in this patch went. (ducks)</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> DaScott: I'm strying to find out what items were suppossedly changed.&nbsp; I'm told that there were some.&nbsp; I guess I have to get midevil on someone</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Baelish&gt; &lt;Thundolfe&gt; Abashi: Despite the pleadings, many MANY well thought out posts and ideas, and generally civility in the way they handle themselves on Gameplay, the players of Rallos Zek have been denied Coin-Only loot. Is there any chance of this issue being reconsidered? If the issue is the +-4 level limit, I believe RZ players would accept an increased limit if it meant coin-only loot. Rallos Zek is a disaster; item-loot is broken.</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Thundolfe: I'm certainly aware of the feelings of those on the boards, however we do not have any plans at this time to make any changes to Rallos' looting policy. I'm sure that many if not most of the peopel there want coin-only, however there is a segment that also enjoys looting.&nbsp; We've already changed 2 servers to coin-only.&nbsp; We right now plan to leave the one as it is....</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Baelish&gt; Abashi, if you are enchanting a bar and move while the spell is being cast the bar goes poof</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Baelish: ACK!!!! is that new?!</P>
<P class=normal><EM>&lt;Baelish&gt; Abashi: not sure heh</EM></P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Are you sure? Hrm.. Ok, well I'll have to talk to the programmer about that one.&nbsp; </P>
<P class=normal><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Ok guys, I'm going to run and see how everything is moving along.</P></blockquote></div>
